Exercise a failing remap prolog: it must abort the remap, convey the error text,
and leave the interpreter usable (return to top level) without running the NGC body.

Re-expressed for gomc: the classic test used a Python prolog that returned
INTERP_ERROR.  gomc removed the embedded Python interpreter, so M400's prolog is a
C interp_ext handler (cmod test_remap_fail, failingprolog) that calls set_error()
and returns INTERP_EXT_ERROR.  The driver runs M400 via MDI; checkresult confirms
the prolog ran and failed, the error text was conveyed (logged by milltask), the
NGC body (notcalled -> o<mark_body>) did NOT run, and a follow-up MDI still works.
